<paragraph blockId="26.[151,750,151,177]" box="[151,750,151,177]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,750,151,177]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
3.2. 
<taxonomicName authority="Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1878" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1878" box="[203,750,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Cosmophylla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
Cosmophylla 
<bibRefCitation author="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C." box="[374,750,151,177]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="1 - 401" refId="ref29469" refString="Brunner von Wattenwyl, C. (1878) Monographie der Phaneropteriden. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch- Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien, 28, 1 - 401." type="journal article" year="1878">Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1878</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,223,393]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
This small group presents 10 species and six genera, with representants from the Neotropics, South American Transition Zone, Andean, Australian and Ethiopic regions. Only the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[953,1048,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Engonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[953,1048,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Engonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was so far recorded, having three currently described species. 
<taxonomicName box="[465,560,296,321]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Engonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[465,560,296,321]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Engonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only genus of Cosmophylla encountered in the neotropics and no species was known to occur in southern 
<collectingCountry box="[521,589,331,357]" name="Brazil" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Brazil</collectingCountry>
so far. Here we provide records for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1878" box="[1001,1171,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Engonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis box="[1001,1171,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Engonia minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and for a possibly new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
